      <section eId="sec_152">
        <num>152</num>
        <heading>Power to administer oaths</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_152__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Each family court judge may\nadminister oaths and take acknowledgments, and may designate an official\nof his court so to do.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_152__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In conducting a hearing under this act, a judge may dispense with\nthe formality of placing a minor under oath before taking his testimony.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
